abstract_ssm: The Sol Yurick Manuscripts for Publication (dated 1944-2006) consists of typed manuscripts and drafts written by novelist Sol Yurick (1925-2013). Yurick was a Brooklyn based writer who was best known for novels portraying poverty and violence in New York City in the 1960s and 1970s. The collection contains drafts and manuscripts of Yurick's published works, as well as manuscripts that were intended for but never reached publication. Other materials in the collection include correspondence, contracts, and royalty statements related to the publication of his novels and stories. It also contains a small amount of personal items such as diaries, personal correspondence, and materials related to Yurick's teaching.
